text: Mitchinamecus Reservoir is a reservoir in Lac-Oscar unorganized territory, Antoine-Labelle Regional County Municipality, Laurentides region, Quebec, Canada. It is formed by the Mitchi-Réal dam, constructed in 1942, across the Mitchinamecus River. The surrounding area is home to moose and is frequented by moose hunters. ==References== Category:Reservoirs in Quebec Category:Lakes of Laurentides
